Mizuho Trust & Banking Co., Ltd. Key Developments

Mizuho Trust & Banking Co., Ltd., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Jun 22, 2017
May 15 17
Mizuho Trust & Banking Co., Ltd., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Jun 22, 2017. Agenda: To change from being a company with board of company auditors to a company with audit and supervisory committee.


Mizuho Trust & Banking Co., Ltd. Announces Board Appointments
May 15 17
Mizuho Trust & Banking Co., Ltd.  has announced the appointment of Masato Monguchi, Hiroyuki Hatano, Masayuki Satake, Kiyotaka Fuke and Ryuta Nakajima as members of the board of directors, which is subject to approval at the Regular General Meeting of Shareholders of the company to be held on June 22, 2017. Mr. Masayuki Satake, Mr. Kiyotaka Fuke and Mr. Ryuta Nakajima qualify as "Outside Director" under the Companies Act.


Mizuho Trust & Banking Co., Ltd. Announces Executive Changes
Mar 9 17
Mizuho Trust & Banking Co., Ltd. announced that Isao Nakamura’s position has been changed from Head of Corporate & Institutional Division, Head of Research & Consulting Unit and Head of Consulting Business Unit, Managing Executive Officer to the new position of Head of Corporate & Institutional Division and Joint Head of Strategic Planning, Financial Control & Accounting Group, Managing Executive Officer; Tatsuya Nakamizo’s position has been changed from General Manager of Nagoya Branch, Executive Officer to the new position of In charge of Trust & Banking, Managing Executive Officer; Toshiro Egawa’s position has been changed from General Manager of Retail & Business Banking Coordination Department, Executive Officer to the new position of Head of Retail & Business Banking Division, Managing Executive Officer; Naoyuki Machinaga’s position has been changed from General Manager of Business Department, Executive Officer to the new position of Head of Research & Consulting Unit, Head of Consulting Business Unit and In charge of Trust & Banking, Managing Executive Officer; Sumito Yasuhara’s position has been changed from General Manager of Trust Business Department V to the new position of General Manager of Trust Business Department V, Executive Officer; Atsunori Tsurumaki’s position has been changed from General Manager of Trust Business Department VII to the new position of General Manager of Nagoya Branch, Executive Officer; Shinichi Iwamura’s position has been changed from General Manager of Investment & Portfolio Management Coordination Department to the new position of General Manager of Investment & Portfolio Management Coordination Department, Executive Officer; Kazuma Ohe’s position has been changed from General Manager of Real Estate Business Coordination Department to the new position of General Manager of Real Estate Business Department IV, Executive Officer; Tomoyasu Kikuno’s position has been changed from General Manager of Branch Administration Department to the new position of General Manager of Fukuoka Branch, Executive Officer; Shinya Matake’s position has been changed from General Manager of Corporate Planning Department to the new position of General Manager of Corporate Planning Department, Executive Officer; and Kazuyuki Akiyama’s position has been changed from General Manager of Consulting Department to the new position of General Manager of Trust Business Department VII, Executive Officer. The company announced the retirement of Makio Muramoto as In charge of Trust & Banking, Managing Executive Officer; Takashi Kamada as Head of Retail & Business Banking Division, Managing Executive Officer; Eijiro Yamanaka as General Manager of Fukuoka Branch, Executive Officer; Masanori Takahata as General Manager of Real Estate Business Department II, Executive Officer; Takashi Otsuka as General Manager of Trust Business Department III, Executive Officer. These all changes are effective from April 1, 2017. The company also announced the retirement of Tsuyoshi Hatsuzawa as Member of the Board of Directors, effective from late June 2017.


